Date: Thu, 28 May 2020 12:50:36 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] Build gdb readline without curses

On Windows/MinGW systems, building readline with ncurses causes input
key handling issues (e.g. backspace and arrow keys do not function
properly).

This patch forces the local readline library used by the gdb to be
built without ncurses (or any curses for that matter).

Signed-off-by: Stephanos Ioannidis <root@stephanos.io>
---
 Makefile.in | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/Makefile.in b/Makefile.in
index 1aabf6ede4..8831a672ff 100644
--- a/Makefile.in
+++ b/Makefile.in
@@ -25511,6 +25511,7 @@ configure-readline:
 	  --srcdir=$${topdir}/$$module_srcdir \
 	  $(HOST_CONFIGARGS) --build=${build_alias} --host=${host_alias} \
 	  --target=${target_alias}  \
+	  --without-curses \
 	  || exit 1
 @endif readline
 
